{
  "bio": [
    "Ed Stack is the executive chairman and largest individual shareholder of Dick's Sporting Goods.",
    "His father, Dick Stack, founded the retailer in 1948 with a $300 loan from his grandmother.",
    "Ed and his siblings bought the company from his father when it only had two stores in upstate New York.",
    "When his father retired in 1984, Ed took over as CEO for 36 years, taking it public in 2002 and stepping down in 2021.",
    "Dick's Sporting Goods now generates more than $12 billion in annual sales across more than 700 stores."
  ],
  "about": [
    "In 2019, Stack announced that Dick's Sporting Goods has eliminated the hunting category, including firearms, from 125 stores."
  ]
